cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about object detection, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel cross-supervised learning pipeline, which involves utilizing image-level annotations and bounding-box-level annotations, and introducing a semantic aggregation strategy. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method using mAP (mean Average Precision), which is a common evaluation metric in information retrieval, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
